        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued June 27 at 6:14PM EDT until June 27 at 6:45PM EDT by NWS Pittsburgh PA</headline>
        <description>At 614 PM EDT, a severe thunderstorm was located near Perryopolis,
or 13 miles west of Connellsville, moving east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.

Locations impacted include...
Connellsville, South Park Township, Jefferson Hills, Monessen,
Clairton, California, Donora, Monongahela, Charleroi, Irwin, West
Newton, Bentleyville, Brownsville, Fredericktown-Millsboro,
Perryopolis, New Eagle, North Belle Vernon, Wickerham
Manor-Fisher, Baidland and Elizabeth.
</description>
        <instruction>Seek shelter inside a well-built structure and stay away from
windows. This storm is capable of producing damaging winds.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead
to flash flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
